tr: make ready for action or use
call in an official matter, such as to attend court

example: muster the courage to do something

value.def: If you summon someone, you order them to come to you.

example.ex: Howe summoned a doctor and hurried over...
example.tran: 豪叫了医生，然后匆忙赶了过来。

example.ex: Suddenly we were summoned to the interview room...
example.tran: 突然我们被叫进了面试的房间。

example.ex: He has been summoned to appear in court on charges of incitement to law-breaking.
example.tran: 因被控教唆犯罪，他已经被传唤出庭。

value.def: If you summon a quality, you make a great effort to have it. For example, if you summon the courage or strength to do something, you make a great effort to be brave or strong, so that you will be able to do it.

example.ex: It took her a full month to summon the courage to tell her mother.
example.tran: 她用了整整一个月才鼓足勇气告诉了妈妈。

example.ex: Painfully shy, he finally summoned up courage to ask her to a game...
example.tran: 他太过腼腆，不过最后终于鼓起勇气邀请她一起去看比赛。

example.ex: We couldn't even summon up the energy to open the envelope.
example.tran: 我们甚至连打开信封的力气都没有了。

value.tran: 鼓起(勇气);振作;使出(力气)
